[h2 id=Tricks:
 
	"Tricks:
	$LF
]h2
[h3 id=Jump-ondetection:
 
	"Jump-on detection:
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"This game seems to use the common jump-on detection algorithm in Mario games: If you are moving downward while hitting some enemy, you jump on it (and don't die unless it is piranha plant or spike top).
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Piranhaplants:
 
	"Piranha plants:
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Piranha plants don't hurt mario while they are popping up from pipe (while going down they do hurt him). 
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Left+Right:
 
	"Left+Right:
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"If you press left+right, Mario instantly changes direction.
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Cornerboosting:
 
	"Cornerboosting:
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"If you hit block suitably from below, you go bit inside it and get ejected. This saves 2 frames a pop if performed correctly.
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=Pickingupbonusesinsideblock:
 
	"Picking up bonuses inside block:
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"If you hit block that's ejecting bonus with sufficient speed, you go bit inside block and hit the bonus, picking it up.
]p
